The Nigerian Centre for Diseases Control (NCDC) has confirmed the two suspected cases of Corona Virus In Kafanchan Negative. LEADERSHIP recalls that a neighbor first raised the alarm on hearing a lady returned from Lagos and concluded they must be infected with the disease since Lagos is one of the State that has highest number of cases of the pandemic. The Chief Medical Director of Sir Patrick Ibrahim Yakowa Dr. Samuel Kure who confirmed the result to Newsmen through the NCDC at the hospital said, the two suspected cases that had caused panic at Ungwan Mission in Jema’a local government area of Kaduna State has been confirmed negative. Dr. Kure cautioned members of the public should desist from taking the laws into their hands. The Council Chairman, Hon. Peter Danjuma Averik said, thank God the result turns out to be negative, calling on the people to be mindful of what they post on social media but report to the appropriate authority. “I am calling on the people if Jema’a Local Government to remain calm and law abiding citizens,” Averik urges.